    {
      "id": "sybil_8_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_8",
      "description": "Available for acquisition is a mechanically sound Mazda RX-7 (FD3S) featuring the iconic 13B-REW power plant. This unit retains its sequential twin-turbocharger configuration, delivering a seamless boost transition through the primary and secondary Hitachi units. The front-midship chassis geometry ensures exceptional balance, complemented by a factory-spec double-wishbone suspension and Torsen LSD. Recent preventative maintenance includes a comprehensive cooling system refresh to manage thermal loads and a vacuum line inspection to ensure peak pneumatic control of the charge relief valves. While the aesthetics reflect its age, the drivetrain remains tight with strong compression across both housings, making it a prime candidate for a driver-focused enthusiast.",
